'From Squeak3.7alpha of ''11 September 2003'' [latest update: #5526] on 9 November 2003 at 10:11:28 am'!"Change Set:		TextMorphInitFix-nkDate:			9 November 2003Author:			Ned KonzClass initialization was causing a walkback.This has been a bug since before 3.0, but had apparently never been tested until another bug caused it to be called."!!TextMorph class methodsFor: 'class initialization' stamp: 'nk 11/9/2003 09:58'!initialize	"TextMorph initialize"		"Initialize constants shared by classes associated with text display."	CaretForm _ (ColorForm extent: 16@5					fromArray: #(2r001100e26 2r001100e26 2r011110e26 2r111111e26 2r110011e26)					offset: -2@0)					colors: (Array with: Color transparent with: Preferences textHighlightColor).	self registerInFlapsRegistry.! !TextMorph initialize!